title: Google\Cloud\Logging\V2\GetCmekSettingsRequest
name: GetCmekSettingsRequest
description:
The parameters to [GetCmekSettings][google.logging.v2.ConfigServiceV2.GetCmekSettings].

See Enabling CMEK for Log Router for more information.

Generated from protobuf message google.logging.v2.GetCmekSettingsRequest

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Required. The resource for which to retrieve CMEK settings. "projects/[PROJECT_ID]/cmekSettings" "organizations/[ORGANIZATION_ID]/cmekSettings" "billingAccounts/[BILLING_ACCOUNT_ID]/cmekSettings" "folders/[FOLDER_ID]/cmekSettings" For example: "organizations/12345/cmekSettings" Note: CMEK for the Log Router can be configured for Google Cloud projects, folders, organizations and billing accounts. Once configured for an organization, it applies to all projects and folders in the Google Cloud organization.
